From: LLTFI-Mac-LLVM20-arm64
Subject: [PATCH] onnx-mlir: LLVM 20.1.0 API compatibility

The official LLTFI fork of onnx-mlir (DependableSystemsLab/onnx-mlir-lltfi
@ b6996967d4) targets LLVM 19. Building it against LLVM 20.1.0 requires
three categories of small changes.

1. `FloatType::getF*(ctx)` was removed; MLIR 20 uses the concrete
   `Float{16,32,64,BF16}Type::get(ctx)` classes directly. Replace all
   call sites (11 source files) with `sed`.

   Affected files (representative):
     - src/Dialect/ONNX/ONNXOps/OpHelper.cpp
     - src/Dialect/ONNX/ONNXOps/Tensor/Slice.cpp
     - src/Dialect/ONNX/ONNXOps/Contrib.cpp
     - src/Dialect/ONNX/ONNXOps/ML/Qlinear*.cpp
     - src/Conversion/ONNXToKrnl/Math/Clip.cpp
     - src/Conversion/ONNXToKrnl/Math/Elementwise.cpp
     - src/Conversion/ONNXToKrnl/ML/RandomNormalLike.cpp
     - src/Conversion/ONNXToKrnl/Tensor/Expand.cpp
     - src/Conversion/ONNXToKrnl/Tensor/Range.cpp
     - src/Conversion/SimplifyShapeRelatedOps.cpp
     - src/Dialect/Mlir/VectorBuilder.cpp

   Pattern:
     `FloatType::getF16(ctx)`  -> `Float16Type::get(ctx)`
     `FloatType::getF32(ctx)`  -> `Float32Type::get(ctx)`
     `FloatType::getF64(ctx)`  -> `Float64Type::get(ctx)`
     `FloatType::getBF16(ctx)` -> `BFloat16Type::get(ctx)`

2. `getStridesAndOffset(t, strides, offset)` is no longer a free function.
   Call it as a method on the type. 2 affected files.

   - src/Conversion/ONNXToKrnl/ML/CategoryMapper.cpp
   - src/Conversion/KrnlToLLVM/KrnlVectorTypeCast.cpp

3. MLIR 20's TOSA dialect changed the `MulOp` `shift` operand from `int`
   to `Value`, and onnx-mlir's `ONNXToTOSA` branch was not updated.
   Temporarily disable the TOSA conversion (StableHLO path remains).

   - src/Conversion/CMakeLists.txt: comment out `add_subdirectory(ONNXToTOSA)`

---
diff --git a/src/Conversion/CMakeLists.txt b/src/Conversion/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/src/Conversion/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/Conversion/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -5,7 +5,7 @@
 add_subdirectory(KrnlToAffine)
 add_subdirectory(KrnlSeqToMemref)
-add_subdirectory(ONNXToTOSA)
+# add_subdirectory(ONNXToTOSA)  # Disabled: TOSA API mismatch with MLIR 20.1.0

 if (ONNX_MLIR_ENABLE_STABLEHLO)
   add_subdirectory(ONNXToStablehlo)
diff --git a/src/Conversion/KrnlToLLVM/KrnlVectorTypeCast.cpp b/src/Conversion/KrnlToLLVM/KrnlVectorTypeCast.cpp
--- a/src/Conversion/KrnlToLLVM/KrnlVectorTypeCast.cpp
+++ b/src/Conversion/KrnlToLLVM/KrnlVectorTypeCast.cpp
@@ -78,7 +78,7 @@
     int64_t offset;
     SmallVector<int64_t, 4> strides;
-    if (failed(getStridesAndOffset(targetType, strides, offset)))
+    if (failed(targetType.getStridesAndOffset(strides, offset)))
       return failure();

     // Unhandled dynamic offset.
diff --git a/src/Conversion/ONNXToKrnl/ML/CategoryMapper.cpp b/src/Conversion/ONNXToKrnl/ML/CategoryMapper.cpp
--- a/src/Conversion/ONNXToKrnl/ML/CategoryMapper.cpp
+++ b/src/Conversion/ONNXToKrnl/ML/CategoryMapper.cpp
@@ -281,7 +281,7 @@
             SmallVector<int64_t, 4> offsets(shape.size(), 0);
             SmallVector<int64_t, 4> strides;
             int64_t alignmentOffset; // not used
-            if (getStridesAndOffset(memRefType, strides, alignmentOffset).failed())
+            if (memRefType.getStridesAndOffset(strides, alignmentOffset).failed())
               llvm_unreachable("Failed to get strides");

NOTE: the Float*Type API replacement covers 11 source files and is best
applied with a recursive `sed -i` rather than as a literal patch diff
(individual hunk context varies). See scripts/build-onnx-mlir.sh for the
exact command.
--
2.39.0
